This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by former President Barack Obama on December 23, 2016. The memorandum establishes an order of succession within the Social Security Administration (SSA). According to the memorandum, in the event that both the Commissioner and Deputy Commissioner of Social Security are unable to perform their duties, the following officials will act as the Commissioner in the listed order: Deputy Commissioner for Operations, Deputy Commissioner for Budget, Finance, Quality, and Management, Deputy Commissioner for Systems, Regional Commissioner (Atlanta), Regional Commissioner (Dallas), Regional Commissioner (San Francisco), and Regional Commissioner (Chicago). The memorandum also includes exceptions and states that the President retains the discretion to designate an acting Commissioner. It revokes a previous memorandum on the same subject issued on October 17, 2014. The memorandum concludes with general provisions clarifying that it does not create any rights or benefits enforceable by any party.